EstimateGenomeSize

Jessie Pelosi

2024-08-09

This script was used to estimate the approximate haploid genome size of i>Lygodium microphyllum using short-read data.

This script was used to estimate the approximate haploid genome size of i>Lygodium microphyllum using short-read data. We will use k-mer frequencies counted with Jellyfish.

This block uses all short-read data, which is approximately 60x coverage. We will use multiple different kmers (21, 31, 41, 51, and 61).

###############All short read data ######################

# 21 mers
spec1_21 <- read.table("./shortreads/21mer_reads.histo")
plot(spec1_21[3:200,], type="l", xlab = "Coverage", ylab = "Frequency", main = "Jellyfish 21mers")
png(file="21mer_jellyfish_shortreads.png", width = 900, height =750)
dev.off()
## quartz_off_screen 
##                 2
points(spec1_21[3:200,])

sum(as.numeric(spec1_21[3:200,1]*spec1_21[3:200,2]))
## [1] 105693178412
max(spec1_21[10:10000,2]) #52x 
## [1] 53867605
Gsize21 <- sum(as.numeric(spec1_21[1:10000,1]*spec1_21[1:10000,2]))/52
# 21 mer : 3.58 Gb @ 52x
#(sum(as.numeric(spec1_21[2:75,1]*spec1_21[2:75,2]))) / (sum(as.numeric(spec1_21[2:10000,1]*spec1_21[2:10000,2])))

To summarize: the approximate haploid genome sizes for each of these kmers is as follows

kmers <- c("21", "31", "41","51", "61")
sizes <- c(Gsize21, Gsize31, Gsize41, Gsize51, Gsize61)
sum <- data.frame(kmers,sizes)
colnames(sum) <- c("kmer", "Haploid Genome Size Estimate")
kable(sum, align = "c") %>% 
  kable_styling(position = "center")
kmer Haploid Genome Size Estimate
21 3579860705
31 4107423692
41 4422333533
51 4646532974
61 4837280140
